diff:1554103319:1554103188:=50,102c50,98%0a%3c #Intuitive GUI%0a%3c #Customizable Toolbars%0a%3c #Bicubic Interpolation with full 32-bit pixel pipeline%0a%3c #Thick Slab for multi-slices CT and MRI (Mean, MIP, Volume Rendering)%0a%3c #ROIs: Polygons, Circles, Pencil, Rectangles, Point, ... with undo/redo support%0a%3c #Key Images%0a%3c #Multi-Buttons and Scroll-wheel mouses supported, including Magic Trackpad support.%0a%3c #Custom CLUT (Color Look-Up Tables)%0a%3c #Custom 3x3 and 5x5 Convolution Filters (Bone filters, ...)%0a%3c #4D Viewer for Cardiac-CT and other temporal series%0a%3c #Image Fusion for PET-CT & SPECT-CT exams with adjustable blending percentage%0a%3c #Image subtraction for XA%0a%3c #Hanging Protocols%0a%3c #Tiles export%0a%3c #2D Image Registration & Reslicing%0a%3c #Workspaces%0a%3c #Plugins support for external functions%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!3D Post-Processing%0a%3c #MPR (Multiplanar Reconstruction) with Thick Slab (Mean, MIP, Volume Rendering)%0a%3c #3D Curved-MPR with Thick Slab%0a%3c #3D MIP (Maximum Intensity Projection)%0a%3c #3D Volume Rendering%0a%3c #3D Surface Rendering%0a%3c #3D ROIs%0a%3c #3D Image Registration%0a%3c #Stereo Vision with Red/Blue glasses%0a%3c #Export any 3D images to Quicktime, TIFF, JPEG%0a%3c #All 3D viewers support 'Image Fusion' for PET-CT exams and '4D mode' for Cardiac-CT.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Optimization%0a%3c #Multi-threaded for multi-processors and multi-core processors support%0a%3c #Asyncronous reading%0a%3c #OpenGL for 2D Viewer and all 3D Viewers%0a%3c #Graphic board accelerated, with 3D texture mapping support%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Expansion & Scientific Research%0a%3c #Miele-LXIV supports a complete dynamic plugins architecture%0a%3c #Access pixels directly in 32-bits float for B&W images or ARGB values for color images%0a%3c #Create and manage windows%0a%3c #Access the entire Cocoa framework%0a%3c #Create and manage OpenGL views%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Based on robust Open-Source components%0a%3c #Cocoa (OpenStep, GNUStep, NextStep)%0a%3c #VTK (Visualization Toolkit)%0a%3c #ITK (Insight Toolkit)%0a%3c #PixelMed (David Clunie)%0a%3c #OpenJPEG%0a%3c #DICOM Offis DCMTK%0a%3c #OpenGL%0a%3c #LibTIFF%0a%3c #LibJPEG%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a---%0a> Intuitive GUI%0a> Customizable Toolbars%0a> Bicubic Interpolation with full 32-bit pixel pipeline%0a> Thick Slab for multi-slices CT and MRI (Mean, MIP, Volume Rendering)%0a> ROIs: Polygons, Circles, Pencil, Rectangles, Point, ... with undo/redo support%0a> Key Images%0a> Multi-Buttons and Scroll-wheel mouses supported, including Magic Trackpad support.%0a> Custom CLUT (Color Look-Up Tables)%0a> Custom 3x3 and 5x5 Convolution Filters (Bone filters, ...)%0a> 4D Viewer for Cardiac-CT and other temporal series%0a> Image Fusion for PET-CT & SPECT-CT exams with adjustable blending percentage%0a> Image subtraction for XA%0a> Hanging Protocols%0a> Tiles export%0a> 2D Image Registration & Reslicing%0a> Workspaces%0a> Plugins support for external functions%0a> 3D Post-Processing%0a> MPR (Multiplanar Reconstruction) with Thick Slab (Mean, MIP, Volume Rendering)%0a> 3D Curved-MPR with Thick Slab%0a> 3D MIP (Maximum Intensity Projection)%0a> 3D Volume Rendering%0a> 3D Surface Rendering%0a> 3D ROIs%0a> 3D Image Registration%0a> Stereo Vision with Red/Blue glasses%0a> Export any 3D images to Quicktime, TIFF, JPEG%0a> All 3D viewers support 'Image Fusion' for PET-CT exams and '4D mode' for Cardiac-CT.%0a> Optimization%0a> Multi-threaded for multi-processors and multi-core processors support%0a> Asyncronous reading%0a> OpenGL for 2D Viewer and all 3D Viewers%0a> Graphic board accelerated, with 3D texture mapping support%0a> Expansion & Scientific Research%0a> Miele-LXIV supports a complete dynamic plugins architecture%0a> Access pixels directly in 32-bits float for B&W images or ARGB values for color images%0a> Create and manage windows%0a> Access the entire Cocoa framework%0a> Create and manage OpenGL views%0a> Based on robust Open-Source components%0a> Cocoa (OpenStep, GNUStep, NextStep)%0a> VTK (Visualization Toolkit)%0a> ITK (Insight Toolkit)%0a> PixelMed (David Clunie)%0a> OpenJPEG%0a> DICOM Offis DCMTK%0a> OpenGL%0a> LibTIFF%0a> LibJPEG%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
